<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFBFFFE1FB77AE948181FDF0" author="Nobrega, P. S. V. &amp; Santos, C. R. M. &amp; Cordeiro, A. P. B. &amp; Martinelli-Lemos, J. M." box="[258,484,506,532]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="227 - 241" refId="ref71517" refString="Nobrega, P. S. V., Santos, C. R. M., Cordeiro, A. P. B. &amp; Martinelli-Lemos, J. M. (2021) Invertebrates assemblage captured by a pink shrimp's fishery on Amazon continental shelf. Latin American Journal of Aquatic Research, 49 (2), 227 - 241. https: // doi. org / 10.3856 / vol 49 - issue 2 - fulltext- 2600." type="journal article" year="2021">
Nóbrega 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1FB1CAE9581C4FDF0" box="[361,417,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24CB1080FFBFFFE1FAB2AD7084E6FCF4" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFBFFFE1FAB2AD7084E6FCF4" blockId="11.[151,1437,289,785]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1FAB2AD70815EFDDC" bold="true" box="[199,315,542,568]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previous records from the coast of São Paulo include only Cananéia (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFBFFFE1FEF1AD708511FDDD" author="Teodoro, S. S. A. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C." box="[1156,1396,542,569]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="244 - 253" refId="ref80385" refString="Teodoro, S. S. A., Terossi, M., Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C. (2016) Discordance in the identification of juvenile pink shrimp (Farfantepenaeus brasiliensis and F. paulensis: Family Penaeidae): an integrative approach using morphology, morphometry and barcoding. Fisheries Research, 183, 244 - 253. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. fishres. 2016.06.009" type="journal article" year="2016">
Teodoro 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1FE9BAD718541FDDC" box="[1262,1316,542,568]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). A remarkably similar species 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFBFFFE1FBA0AD2C8448FDB8" authority="Tavares &amp; Gusmao, 2016" authorityName="Tavares &amp; Gusmao" authorityYear="2016" box="[469,1069,578,604]" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Farfantepenaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isabelae">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1FBA0AD2C829FFDB8" box="[469,762,578,604]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Farfantepenaeus isabelae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFBFFFE1F970AD2C8448FDB8" author="Tavares, C. &amp; Gusmao, J." box="[773,1069,578,604]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="505 - 516" refId="ref79863" refString="Tavares, C. &amp; Gusmao, J. (2016) Description of a new Penaeidae (Decapoda: Dendrobranchiata) species, Farfantepenaeus isabelae sp. nov. Zootaxa, 4171 (3), 505 - 516. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4171.3.6" type="journal article" year="2016">Tavares &amp; Gusmão, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from one of the two morphotypes of 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFBFFFE1FBF3AD098191FD64" baseAuthorityName="Perez Farfante" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[390,500,614,640]" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Farfantepenaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1FBF3AD098191FD64" box="[390,500,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">F. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
just after that record. 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFBFFFE1F880AD088441FD65" author="Tavares, C. &amp; Gusmao, J." box="[757,1060,614,641]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="505 - 516" refId="ref79863" refString="Tavares, C. &amp; Gusmao, J. (2016) Description of a new Penaeidae (Decapoda: Dendrobranchiata) species, Farfantepenaeus isabelae sp. nov. Zootaxa, 4171 (3), 505 - 516. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4171.3.6" type="journal article" year="2016">Tavares &amp; Gusmão (2016)</bibRefCitation>
reported that it was not possible to confirm the identification of the specimen presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFBFFFE1F94AADE48450FD41" author="Teodoro, S. S. A. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C." box="[831,1077,650,677]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="244 - 253" refId="ref80385" refString="Teodoro, S. S. A., Terossi, M., Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C. (2016) Discordance in the identification of juvenile pink shrimp (Farfantepenaeus brasiliensis and F. paulensis: Family Penaeidae): an integrative approach using morphology, morphometry and barcoding. Fisheries Research, 183, 244 - 253. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. fishres. 2016.06.009" type="journal article" year="2016">
Teodoro 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1F9D3ADE583BFFD40" box="[934,986,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
since molecular analyzes were performed in distinct regions of mitochondrial DNA. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFBFFFE1F917ADC0845AFD2C" author="Franca, N. F. C. &amp; Alencar, C. E. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Freire, F. A. M." box="[866,1087,686,712]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="497 - 508" refId="ref62519" refString="Franca, N. F. C., Alencar, C. E., Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Freire, F. A. M. (2020) Filling biogeographic gaps about the shrimp Farfantepenaeus isabelae Tavares &amp; Gusmao, 2016 (Decapoda: Penaeidae) in South America. Zootaxa, 4718 (4), 497 - 508. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4718.4.4" type="journal article" year="2020">
<collectingCountry id="14C6039BFFBFFFE1F917ADC083CBFD2C" box="[866,942,686,712]" name="France" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">França</collectingCountry>
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1F9C0ADC18383FD2C" box="[949,998,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. (2020)
</bibRefCitation>
confirmed the identification of a single specimen collected by 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFBFFFE1FB80ADBC8286FD09" author="Teodoro, S. S. A. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C." box="[501,739,722,749]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="244 - 253" refId="ref80385" refString="Teodoro, S. S. A., Terossi, M., Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C. (2016) Discordance in the identification of juvenile pink shrimp (Farfantepenaeus brasiliensis and F. paulensis: Family Penaeidae): an integrative approach using morphology, morphometry and barcoding. Fisheries Research, 183, 244 - 253. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. fishres. 2016.06.009" type="journal article" year="2016">
Teodoro 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1F82CADBD82EFFD08" box="[601,650,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFBFFFE1F97DADBD8310FD08" baseAuthorityName="Perez Farfante" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[776,885,722,748]" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Farfantepenaeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1F97DADBD8310FD08" box="[776,885,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">F. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sequence accession number (GenBank): CCDB 4676—16S (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFBFFFE1FB50AD9881CDFCF4" box="[293,424,758,784]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MF490143" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">MF490143</accessionNumber>
), COI (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFBFFFE1FB8EAD98821FFCF5" box="[507,634,758,785]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KX421864" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">KX421864</accessionNumber>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFBFFFE1F8FAAD988315FCF4" author="Teodoro, S. S. A. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C." box="[655,880,758,784]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="244 - 253" refId="ref80385" refString="Teodoro, S. S. A., Terossi, M., Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Costa, R. C. (2016) Discordance in the identification of juvenile pink shrimp (Farfantepenaeus brasiliensis and F. paulensis: Family Penaeidae): an integrative approach using morphology, morphometry and barcoding. Fisheries Research, 183, 244 - 253. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. fishres. 2016.06.009" type="journal article" year="2016">
Teodoro 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1F880AD998342FCF4" box="[757,807,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFBFFFE1F90EAD988412FCF4" author="Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Negri, M. &amp; Buranelli, R. C. &amp; Robles, R. &amp; Magalhaes, T. &amp; Tamburus, A. F. &amp; Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J." box="[891,1143,758,784]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="805 - 815" refId="ref68637" refString="Mantelatto, F. L., Terossi, M., Negri, M., Buranelli, R. C., Robles, R., Magalhaes, T., Tamburus, A. F., Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J. (2018) DNA sequence database as a tool to identify decapod crustaceans on the Sao Paulo coastline. Mitochondrial DNA Part A: DNA Mapping, Sequencing and Analysis, 29 (5), 805 - 815. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24701394.2017.1365848" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mantelatto 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFBFFFE1F98EAD998448FCF4" box="[1019,1069,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
